.@SafaricomPLC has been distributing at least 80% of its net income to shareholders, leaving the remaining 20% for reinvestment in infrastructure and retained earnings, which now stand at Sh133.7B. The telco could tap retained earnings to partially fund its Ethiopian commitments.

In its early life as a publicly-traded company, @SafaricomPLC used to fund its growth through debt, but it weaned itself off medium to long-term debt as its cash generation exceeded reinvestment needs.
.@SafaricomPLC noted that it held cash and cash equivalents of Sh26.4B in the review period, placing its net debt at Sh50.5B.
